---
description: Data protection and privacy standards for handling sensitive information in prompts and AI workflows
alwaysApply: true
---

data-protection-standards:

- Never expose personally identifiable information (PII) in prompts without protection or redaction.
- Apply masking or tokenization to sensitive data before sending to external AI models.
- Use Protegrity's semantic guardrails to evaluate conversation risk and PII exposure.
- Document data sensitivity classifications in code comments.
- Implement input validation and sanitization for user-provided data.
- Configure appropriate protection methods based on data sensitivity level.
- Keep audit logs of data protection operations.
- Use synthetic data for testing and development to avoid exposing production data.
